e trauma of war. She calls on the reader to recognize and bear witness to the impact of deeper forms of violence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021vPersonal narratives, Afghan. 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021xWomenxSocial conditions. 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021. 0aCollective memoryzAfghanistan. 0aCollective memoryzCanada. 0aWomen and warzAfghanistan. 0aWomenzAfghanistanxSocial conditions. 0aWomenzAfghanistanxSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266760040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442667600423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442667600/original  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK